value.value: Sensory system responsible for the perception of light.
Portion of tissue that is the cavity-containing primordium of the central nervous system, developing from the neural rod in the late segmentation period.
A layer separating the inner face of the dermis from the subjacent muscle cells. It is covered on both sides by a basement membrane.  It contains pigment cells.
Tooth row that is the ventralmost row of teeth on ceratobranchial 5 bone.
Sensory system responsible for the perception of spatial orientation and auditory stimuli.
Tooth row that is the mediodorsal row of teeth on ceratobranchial 5 bone, located between the dorsal tooth row and ventral tooth row.
Tooth row that is the dorsalmost row of teeth on ceratobranchial 5 bone.
Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the anteriormost tooth in the ventral tooth row.
Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the posteriormost tooth in the ventral tooth row.
Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 3V and anterior to tooth 5V in the ventral tooth row.
Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 1V and anterior to tooth 3V in the ventral tooth row.
Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 2V and anterior to tooth 4V in the ventral tooth row.
Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the anteriormost tooth in the mediodorsal tooth row.
Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 1MD and anterior to tooth 3MD in the mediodorsal tooth row.
Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the anteriormost tooth in the dorsal tooth row.
Sensory system responsible for olfaction.  Olfaction involves the detection of chemical composition of an organism's ambient medium by chemoreceptors.
Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the posteriormost tooth in the dorsal tooth row.
Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the posteriormost tooth in the mediodorsal tooth row.
Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 2MD and anterior to tooth 4MD in the mediodorsal tooth row.
Placode that develops into a tooth. The placode is a thickening of the pharyngeal epithelium.
Musculature part of the anal fin.

Nervous system that  is involved primarily with the internal regulation of the gustatory processes. In most vertebrates the enteric neurons form two layers of ganglionic plexuses located along the entire length of the gastrointestinal tract.
Dorsolateral placode that gives rise to the posterior lateral line.

A migrating group of cells originating from the posterior lateral line placode.  The primordium deposits seven to nine neuromasts and interneuromasts between them during its posterior migration to the tail.
Anatomical system that produces, transports and secretes peptides.
System that provides protection against foreign and abnormal cells and removes cellular debris.
Paired fin that is located in the thoracic region of the body.
Median fin that is located posterior to the anus.
Supraneural located between vertebra 6 and 7.
Supraneural located between vertebra 5 and 6.
Supraneural located between  vertebra 4 and 5.
Supraneural located between vertebra 8 and 9.
Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to the neurocranium.
Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 1.
Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 2.
Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 3.

Thin, rod-shaped, anteroventrally directed membrane bone that develops as a separate outgrowth  from the cartilage parapophysis of the fourth vertebra; develops ventrally to curve around the anterior head of the swim bladder. It articulates with the tripus at the tripus-swim bladder connection. Often termed a fifth Weberian ossicle.

definition.value: The os suspensorium is similar in shape to a rib, but the other ribs in Danio develop as separate ossifications that grow toward and articulate with the parapophyses.

value.value: Cartilaginous larval structure dorsal to the four anterior-most vertebrae, which forms the connection between neural arches and supraneurals in the Weberian apparatus.  Located dorsal to the neural tube.
Median fin that is located on the dorsal surface of the fish.
Epithelium lining the pharynx consisting largely of simple columnar epithelium with a short segment (1mm) of stratified squamous epithelium on the ventral side.
Embryonic structure that is the dome of cytoplasm that segregates from the yolk toward the animal pole during and after the one cell-stage, and which undergoes cleavage.

Embryonic structure that is composed of the cellular part of the embryo, excluding the yolk cell, derived from the blastodisc by early morphogenesis; refers particularly to the time when the cell array is sheet-like, between 30%-epiboly and the end of gastrulation.
